This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Status conference on December 7, 2022 at 10:00 am.
Due to ongoing CV trial, status conf adj to 12/7/22 @ 10am
from Behavioral Health Jail Diversion Program

10:43 AM Prosecuting attorney Alexander Huber in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Jordan G. Ibendahl in court.  Attorney Seth Elijah Johnson in court for Jordan G. Ibendahl. Clerk N. Nobile.
MINUTES: Victim rights compliance. Attorney Johnson  states that the DE has been accepted into the program, but is requesting an adjournment for reasons set forth on the record. The State does not object. Court adjourns to check on the status of the program proceeding do to funding.
Status conference scheduled for October 28, 2022 at 08:30 am.

02:39 PM   State appears by Attorney Alexandra Smathers. Defendant, Jordan G. Ibendahl, appeared with Attorney Seth Elijah Johnson.   Clerk N. Nobile.
MINUTES:   Victim rights compliance. Attorney Johnson is requesting another adjournment as the DE has been referred to the Jail Diversion Program, but he has not completed the application process. The State does not object to adjourning to see if the DE is accepted into the Mental Health Treatment program. Court adjourns.  Status conference scheduled for October 5, 2022 at 10:30 am.

08:49 AM  State appears by Attorney Alexandra Smathers. Defendant, Jordan G. Ibendahl, appeared with Attorney Seth Elijah Johnson.  Clerk N. Nobile.
MINUTES: Attorney Johnson is requesting an adjournment for reasons set forth on the record. ADA Smathers does not object to one more adjournment, but requests that this matter be scheduled on her next rotation. Court adjourns.  Status conference scheduled for August 24, 2022 at 02:30 pm.

Minutes:  Judge Kluka acting for Branch 3.  Clerk/T. Lema.  ADA Alex Smathers appeared for the State.  Deft appeared along w/Atty Seth Johnson.  VRC.  Complainants present in court.  Attys are working towards resolution - deft to apply to Mental Health Treatment program.  Individual that handles the applications to this program is out until the middle of July.  Status set for 8/4/22 @ 8:30am.  JS date removed from court's calendar.
No disposition. Leave on for next scheduled court activity.
